    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Amaranth, (genus Amaranthus), genus of 60–70 species of flowering plants in the family Amaranthaceae, distributed nearly worldwide and species are useful as food crops and are grown both for their leaves and for their edible seeds.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
